- Follow PEP 8 for Python code.
- Use type hints for all function signatures and important variables.
- Write clear and concise docstrings for all public modules, classes, and functions, preferably in Google style.
- Aim for high test coverage. New features should include corresponding unit tests.
- Keep functions and methods short and focused on a single responsibility.
- Avoid overly complex list comprehensions or lambda functions if they harm readability.
- Comment non-obvious code sections.
